---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Platform overview"
  description="Praxnote is one workspace for behavioral health — documentation, the practice's daily work, and the quiet protections underneath. Four roles share all of it."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="The workspace"
    title="One workspace. <em>Four people who share it.</em>"
    lede="Praxnote isn't a notes tool with billing bolted on, or a billing tool with notes bolted on. It's one workspace, built end to end for behavioral-health practices, with the four people who actually run a practice in mind from the start."
  >
    <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request access</a>
    <a href="/security" class="btn btn-secondary">Read the security overview</a>
  </PageHeader>

  <section class="prose">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p>
        At the front is the <strong>clinical work</strong>. Fourteen editable templates draft
        session notes in five formats, treatment plans in five formats, referral and discharge
        letters, case conceptualizations, assessment-result letters in clinician or client
        voice. Each template is written in plain language and can be adjusted by the practice
        to match how you actually write. The version in effect at the moment of a draft is
        kept with the document.
      </p>
      <p>
        Around it is the <strong>day-to-day of running a practice</strong>. The supervision
        screen that lets a supervisor clear a Friday's notes in twenty minutes. The calendar
        that lets clinicians set their availability and clients book against it. Billing that
        sends an invoice and a payment link in a tap, with the right rate for the right
        clinician. The client portal that opens with a single link in a text message. These
        are not add-ons. They share one history, one set of permissions, and one place to
        look when you need to.
      </p>
      <p>
        Underneath is the <strong>quiet work that keeps it all safe</strong>. Client information
        is encrypted, both when it sits and when it moves. Every read and every change is recorded.
        A right-to-be-forgotten request can be carried out cleanly, even alongside the records-retention
        rules that apply at the same time. The portal speaks more than one language. A private,
        PIN-locked copy of what you need can live on a clinician's device for the days when the
        wifi doesn't. None of this is visible most of the time. All of it is true all of the time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Four roles share the workspace: <strong>clinician, supervisor, practice admin, and
        client</strong>. Each sees what their role calls for. The owner who is also a clinician
        — or the supervisor who still carries a half caseload — doesn't need two accounts. One
        identity, a clear visual cue for which hat is on, and a record that knows which hat
        took each action.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="diagram">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="stack" aria-labelledby="stack-caption">
        <div class="layer layer--top">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">01</span>
            <h3>The clinical work</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>14 editable templates · session notes (SOAP, DAP, BIRP, narrative, custom) · treatment plans (PBT/EEMM, standard, CBT, DBT, simple) · diagnoses · case conceptualization · referral, discharge, and leave-of-absence letters · twenty validated assessments</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="layer layer--mid">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">02</span>
            <h3>The day-to-day</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>supervision screen · scheduling and waitlist · cash-pay billing with autopay · client portal with one-tap sign-in · email and text templates · session types and rates per clinician</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="layer layer--bottom">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">03</span>
            <h3>The quiet work</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>encryption when records sit and when they move · a complete history of who did what when · right-to-be-forgotten that doesn't break records-retention · a multilingual portal · a PIN-locked offline copy for clinicians on the road · audit-ready exports</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption id="stack-caption">One workspace. One history. One set of permissions. Same encryption everywhere.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <aside class="roles-rail">
        <span class="rail-label">Four roles share all of it</span>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/solutions/solo-clinicians">Clinician</a></li>
          <li><a href="/solutions/supervisors">Supervisor</a></li>
          <li><a href="/solutions/practice-admins">Practice admin</a></li>
          <li><a href="/features/client-portal">Client</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    eyebrow="See it on your practice"
    heading="A walk-through, on your terms."
    body="Bring a recent session, a billing batch, a supervision queue, or an erasure scenario. We'll walk Praxnote through the actual work you do."
    primaryHref="/demo"
    primaryLabel="Book a walk-through"
    secondaryHref="/pricing"
    secondaryLabel="See pricing"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Long-form narrative */
  .prose { padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0 clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); }
  .prose p {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.4vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--stone-900); font-weight: 600; }

  /* Layered diagram */
  .diagram { padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem) 0 clamp(4rem, 7vw, 6rem); }
  .stack {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .layer {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.85rem clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .layer:last-of-type { border-bottom: 0; }
  .layer--top { background: var(--surface-card); }
  .layer--mid { background: var(--paper-warm); }
  .layer--bottom { background: var(--surface-ink); color: var(--paper-warm); border-bottom: 0; }
  .layer-rail { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .layer-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--brand-teal);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-num { color: var(--brand-teal-soft); }
  .layer-rail h3 {
    font-size: 1.55rem;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--stone-900);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-rail h3 { color: var(--paper); }
  .layer-body p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-body p { color: rgba(250, 247, 242, 0.72); }

  .stack figcaption {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--paper);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--stone-500);
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .layer { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.85rem; padding: 1.5rem; }
    .layer-rail { flex-direction: row; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.85rem; }
  }

  /* Roles rail (separate, after the stack) */
  .roles-rail {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.75rem);
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .rail-label {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
  }
  .roles-rail ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .roles-rail li { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--stone-800); }
  .roles-rail a {
    color: var(--stone-800);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--hairline-strong);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }
  .roles-rail a:hover { color: var(--brand-teal-dark); border-bottom-color: var(--brand-teal); }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .roles-rail { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
